g.text: * Token bucket (filled with tokens at some interval)
* Leaky bucket (request put in a queue - constant rate to a service)
* Fixed window counter (can allow double requests)
* Sliding window log (all requests allowed/rejected logged with timestamp and counted)
* Sliding window counter (count in current time + average of portion in prev window)
will know that 3 tokens were consumed by others,
so real available tokens for clientB on this host
Ratelimiter can be more or less precise,
tradeoff of throttling less requests than expected
